page.title: 10Wimbledon Common (3) Nature
page.content: There are many examples of naturally seeded trees and they include Alder, Ash, Aspen, Beech, Black Poplar, Elm, Elder, False Acacia, Hawthorn, Holm Oak, Chestnut, Lime, Lombardy Poplar, London Plane; Common, Scarlet and Turkey Oaks; Silver Birch, Sycamore and Willow. Birds seen on the Common and Heath include: Wood pigeon, Magpie, Jay, Thrush, Robin, Blackbird, Starling, Chaffinch, Blue Tit, Moorhen, Greenfinch, Pied Wagtail, Mallard and Coot. Kingsmere, Queen's Mere, Bluegate Gravel Pit and Rushmere Pond are all teeming with wild life. Rushes, sedges, bracken, ferns and fungi all abound. A golf course covers a large area. The Ranger looks after over a million trees and the biggest nuisance is vandalism and the deliberate burning of trees. Silver birches and sycamore spread too easily and squirrels damage trees.cont.
